1
00:03:26,781 --> 00:03:28,883
All were transported?

2
00:03:28,884 --> 00:03:30,125
Almost.

3
00:03:30,326 --> 00:03:32,408
"Almost."

4
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:34,650
Sir, with all due respect,

5
00:03:34,651 --> 00:03:36,012
are you sure this
is our best option?

6
00:03:36,013 --> 00:03:37,895
I mean, why can't we just
correct the problem?

7
00:03:37,896 --> 00:03:40,138
Because my fuckin' nephew

8
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,822
killed a dog.

9
00:03:44,264 --> 00:03:45,746
And he stole a car.

10
00:03:46,707 --> 00:03:49,226
A car

11
00:03:49,227 --> 00:03:52,307
which currently is
among our inventory.

12
00:03:56,147 --> 00:03:59,027
So we're giving
everything up for a car?

13
00:04:00,827 --> 00:04:02,866
It's not just a car.

14
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:05,507
It is John wick's car.

15
00:04:06,707 --> 00:04:08,467
Oh.

16
00:04:15,267 --> 00:04:17,187
Sir, why don't we
just give it back?

17
00:04:18,107 --> 00:04:20,147
He killed my nephew.

18
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:22,907
My brother.

19
00:04:24,587 --> 00:04:26,707
<i>And a dozen of my men.</i>

20
00:04:28,587 --> 00:04:30,707
Over his car.

21
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:33,107
And a puppy.

22
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,706
And you...

23
00:04:37,707 --> 00:04:39,946
You think he will stop now?

24
00:04:39,947 --> 00:04:41,187
<i>Hmm?</i>

25
00:04:43,787 --> 00:04:46,346
<i>Sir, he's one man.</i>

26
00:04:46,347 --> 00:04:48,147
Why don't we just eliminate him?

27
00:04:52,107 --> 00:04:53,986
John wick

28
00:04:53,987 --> 00:04:56,387
<i>is a man of focus...</i>

29
00:05:00,107 --> 00:05:01,587
Commitment...

30
00:05:07,987 --> 00:05:11,027
And sheer fuckin' will!

31
00:05:26,347 --> 00:05:28,146
He once killed three
men in a bar...

32
00:05:28,147 --> 00:05:30,346
With a pencil. I know.
I've heard the story.

33
00:05:30,347 --> 00:05:32,267
With a fucking pencil!

34
00:05:33,147 --> 00:05:35,067
Who the fuck can do that?

35
00:05:37,107 --> 00:05:38,907
I can assure you

36
00:05:40,427 --> 00:05:44,266
<i>that the stories you
hear about this man,</i>

37
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:50,147
if nothing else, has
been watered down.

38
00:06:05,217 --> 00:06:08,977
You have my car...

39
00:06:12,097 --> 00:06:14,797
THE BOOGEYMAN.

40
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:13,777
Peace.

41
00:12:13,778 --> 00:12:17,978
Can a man like you know peace?

42
00:12:19,558 --> 00:12:22,258
Why not?

43
00:12:29,568 --> 00:12:31,768
Peace.

44
00:12:41,658 --> 00:12:44,358
Enjoy your retirement...

45
00:12:44,868 --> 00:12:46,268
Mr. wick.

46
00:15:09,228 --> 00:15:10,788
Hey, buddy.

47
00:15:17,388 --> 00:15:18,868
Hey.

48
00:15:26,108 --> 00:15:27,508
Good dog.

49
00:15:42,028 --> 00:15:43,587
<i>What are you doing, John?</i>

50
00:15:43,588 --> 00:15:44,788
<i>Looking at you.</i>

51
00:15:45,388 --> 00:15:46,627
<i>What are you doing?</i>

52
00:15:46,628 --> 00:15:48,308
<i>I'm waiting for you.</i>

53
00:15:49,068 --> 00:15:50,388
<i>Come here.</i>

54
00:16:05,028 --> 00:16:06,548
Hey, boy.

55
00:16:30,668 --> 00:16:32,588
Nice peaceful place
you got here.

56
00:16:33,588 --> 00:16:35,548
Hey, Aurelio. Hey.

57
00:16:39,508 --> 00:16:42,708
John, what the hell? I
thought you loved this car.

58
00:16:43,788 --> 00:16:45,067
What do you think?

59
00:16:45,068 --> 00:16:48,267
Well, your motor's
about to fall out

60
00:16:48,268 --> 00:16:50,627
and the chassis's all bent up,

61
00:16:50,628 --> 00:16:52,547
the driveshaft is all destroyed.

62
00:16:52,548 --> 00:16:53,707
And I don't know if you noticed,

63
00:16:53,708 --> 00:16:56,227
but you got a crack
in your windshield.

64
00:16:56,228 --> 00:16:58,668
I mean... What do I think?

65
00:16:59,788 --> 00:17:01,308
I could fix this.

66
00:17:02,668 --> 00:17:04,347
Thanks for finding her.

67
00:17:04,348 --> 00:17:05,987
Not a problem, man. I
just made a few calls.

68
00:17:05,988 --> 00:17:07,348
No big deal.

69
00:17:09,868 --> 00:17:12,267
Let me know when it's fixed.

70
00:17:12,268 --> 00:17:15,787
All right. It'll be
ready Christmas...

71
00:17:15,788 --> 00:17:17,268
2030.

72
00:18:52,468 --> 00:18:53,708
Ciao, John.

73
00:18:54,708 --> 00:18:55,988
Santino.

74
00:19:01,488 --> 00:19:04,188
May I come in?

75
00:19:05,678 --> 00:19:07,878
Of course.

76
00:19:14,688 --> 00:19:16,388
Coffee?

77
00:19:21,389 --> 00:19:22,629
Good to see you.

78
00:19:23,269 --> 00:19:24,749
Good to see you.

79
00:19:43,789 --> 00:19:46,349
I was sorry to hear
about your wife, John.

80
00:19:48,229 --> 00:19:49,709
Thank you.

81
00:19:51,589 --> 00:19:53,429
Hi.

82
00:19:55,309 --> 00:19:58,069
And the dog, does
he have a name?

83
00:19:58,949 --> 00:20:00,149
No.

84
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:12,589
Listen, John, with
all sincerity...

85
00:20:14,309 --> 00:20:15,548
I don't want to be here.

86
00:20:15,549 --> 00:20:18,188
Please, don't.

87
00:20:18,189 --> 00:20:20,389
I'm asking you not to do this.

88
00:20:21,029 --> 00:20:22,389
I'm sorry.

89
00:20:26,669 --> 00:20:30,348
No one gets out and comes back

90
00:20:30,349 --> 00:20:32,669
without repercussions.

91
00:20:34,389 --> 00:20:37,189
I do this with a
heavy heart, John.

92
00:20:39,949 --> 00:20:43,788
But remember, if
not for what I did

93
00:20:43,789 --> 00:20:46,828
on the night of your
impossible task,

94
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:50,668
you wouldn't be here
right now, like this.

95
00:20:50,669 --> 00:20:53,548
This is because of me.

96
00:20:53,549 --> 00:20:55,509
This, in part, is mine.

97
00:20:55,909 --> 00:20:58,188
Take it back.

98
00:20:58,189 --> 00:21:00,188
"Take it back"? Take it back.

99
00:21:00,189 --> 00:21:04,028
A marker is no
small thing, John.

100
00:21:04,029 --> 00:21:07,148
For a man to Grant a
marker to another,

101
00:21:07,149 --> 00:21:09,909
is to bind a soul
to a blood oath.

102
00:21:13,629 --> 00:21:15,669
Find someone else.

103
00:21:18,869 --> 00:21:20,428
Listen to me.

104
00:21:20,429 --> 00:21:22,668
What is this? Hmm?

105
00:21:22,669 --> 00:21:26,228
Do you remember?
This is your blood.

106
00:21:26,229 --> 00:21:29,269
You came to me. I helped you.

107
00:21:30,109 --> 00:21:32,748
And if you don't do this,

108
00:21:32,749 --> 00:21:35,189
you know the consequences.

109
00:21:36,909 --> 00:21:39,069
I'm not that guy anymore.

110
00:21:42,989 --> 00:21:45,389
You are always that guy, John.

111
00:21:49,509 --> 00:21:51,269
I can't help you.

112
00:22:02,669 --> 00:22:04,229
I'm sorry.

113
00:22:16,589 --> 00:22:19,589
Yes. You're right.

114
00:22:20,149 --> 00:22:21,389
You can't.

115
00:22:24,589 --> 00:22:26,508
But he can.

116
00:22:26,509 --> 00:22:28,189
I'll see you soon, John.

117
00:22:39,549 --> 00:22:42,309
You have a beautiful home, John.

118
00:24:53,469 --> 00:24:55,669
Well, good evenin', John.

119
00:24:56,309 --> 00:24:57,749
Hey, Jimmy.

120
00:24:59,669 --> 00:25:01,349
Gas leak?

121
00:25:03,029 --> 00:25:04,669
Yeah, gas leak.

122
00:25:06,109 --> 00:25:07,909
You workin' again?

123
00:25:10,269 --> 00:25:12,029
I'll see you, Jimmy.

124
00:25:12,869 --> 00:25:14,949
Come on, boy.

125
00:25:17,789 --> 00:25:19,589
Good night, John.

126
00:25:21,469 --> 00:25:23,349
Oh, shit.

127
00:26:04,669 --> 00:26:06,788
I'd like to see the manager.

128
00:26:06,789 --> 00:26:09,549
How good to see you again
so soon, Mr. wick.

129
00:26:10,309 --> 00:26:11,789
Shall I announce you?

130
00:26:12,349 --> 00:26:13,829
Yes, please.

131
00:26:14,669 --> 00:26:16,309
Stay.

132
00:26:23,629 --> 00:26:26,229
Mr. wick is on his
way to see you, sir.

133
00:26:38,669 --> 00:26:40,269
Impeccable.

134
00:26:41,869 --> 00:26:45,189
Put these into circulation.

135
00:26:58,229 --> 00:26:59,629
Where is he?

136
00:27:01,229 --> 00:27:03,068
Thank you, my friend.

137
00:27:03,069 --> 00:27:05,309
Beautiful work. Beautiful.

138
00:27:11,949 --> 00:27:13,869
What are you doing, Jonathan?

139
00:27:14,869 --> 00:27:16,908
He burned my house down.

140
00:27:16,909 --> 00:27:20,469
You rejected his marker.
You're lucky he stopped there.

141
00:27:21,509 --> 00:27:23,108
What the hell were you thinking,

142
00:27:23,109 --> 00:27:26,028
giving a marker to a man
like Santino d'Antonio?

143
00:27:26,029 --> 00:27:28,188
It was the only way
I could get out.

144
00:27:28,189 --> 00:27:31,269
Oh. You call this "out"?

145
00:27:32,789 --> 00:27:34,988
What did you think
was gonna happen?

146
00:27:34,989 --> 00:27:36,868
What did you expect? Huh?

147
00:27:36,869 --> 00:27:40,629
Did you really think this day
was never going to come? Hmm?

148
00:27:42,669 --> 00:27:44,589
What does he want you to do?

149
00:27:46,309 --> 00:27:47,789
I didn't ask.

150
00:27:48,509 --> 00:27:49,909
I just said no.

151
00:27:52,869 --> 00:27:56,108
Two rules that cannot
be broken, Jonathan.

152
00:27:56,109 --> 00:27:57,868
No blood on continental grounds,

153
00:27:57,869 --> 00:28:01,108
and every marker
must be honored.

154
00:28:01,109 --> 00:28:05,508
Now, while my judgment comes
in the form of excommunicado,

155
00:28:05,509 --> 00:28:09,008
the high table demand
a more severe outcome

156
00:28:09,009 --> 00:28:11,209
if their traditions are refused.

157
00:28:11,789 --> 00:28:13,709
I have no choice?

158
00:28:14,669 --> 00:28:16,908
You dishonor the marker,
you die.

159
00:28:16,909 --> 00:28:18,868
You kill the holder of
the marker, you die.

160
00:28:18,869 --> 00:28:21,189
You run, you die.

161
00:28:22,269 --> 00:28:24,789
This is what you
agreed to, Jonathan.

162
00:28:25,229 --> 00:28:27,189
Do what the man asks.

163
00:28:28,389 --> 00:28:29,868
Be free.

164
00:28:29,869 --> 00:28:32,308
Then, if you want
to go after him,

165
00:28:32,309 --> 00:28:34,508
burn his house
down, be my guest.

166
00:28:34,509 --> 00:28:35,989
But until then...

167
00:28:38,389 --> 00:28:39,749
Rules.

168
00:28:40,469 --> 00:28:43,468
Exactly. Rules.

169
00:28:43,469 --> 00:28:45,949
Without them, we'd
live with the animals.

170
00:28:53,829 --> 00:28:56,428
Do you board?

171
00:28:56,429 --> 00:28:59,589
I'm sorry to say, sir, but
this facility does not.

172
00:29:01,029 --> 00:29:04,108
I, however, would be
willing to accept

173
00:29:04,109 --> 00:29:06,549
the responsibility,
should you wish.

174
00:29:07,989 --> 00:29:09,348
Appreciate that.

175
00:29:09,349 --> 00:29:11,109
Does he have a name, sir?

176
00:29:11,229 --> 00:29:12,588
No.

177
00:29:12,589 --> 00:29:14,588
Good dog.

178
00:29:14,589 --> 00:29:16,189
Stay.

179
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:20,669
This was my father's collection.

180
00:30:20,670 --> 00:30:24,190
I see little more than just
paint on canvas, of course.

181
00:30:26,110 --> 00:30:28,230
But I do find myself here.

182
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:31,510
Please.

183
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:45,869
I didn't want to do this, John.

184
00:30:45,870 --> 00:30:49,430
Had you stayed retired, I
would have respected it.

185
00:30:51,390 --> 00:30:53,469
Look at you.

186
00:30:53,470 --> 00:30:55,790
You're thinkin' about
it, aren't you?

187
00:30:56,710 --> 00:31:00,430
You're counting exits, guards...

188
00:31:01,950 --> 00:31:03,830
Could you get to me in time?

189
00:31:05,870 --> 00:31:07,950
How would you do it, I wonder?

190
00:31:09,750 --> 00:31:10,990
That woman's pen?

191
00:31:13,070 --> 00:31:14,310
His cane?

192
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:17,710
Maybe his glasses?

193
00:31:18,510 --> 00:31:20,150
My hands.

194
00:31:20,910 --> 00:31:22,829
Ah.

195
00:31:22,830 --> 00:31:25,189
How exciting.

196
00:31:25,190 --> 00:31:27,150
Yet, you know you
cannot, can you?

197
00:31:28,070 --> 00:31:31,789
I told you I needed that guy,

198
00:31:31,790 --> 00:31:34,230
the way you are looking
at me right now.

199
00:31:34,990 --> 00:31:37,549
I needed the boogeyman.

200
00:31:37,550 --> 00:31:38,869
I needed John wick.

201
00:31:38,870 --> 00:31:42,030
Just tell me what you want.

202
00:31:46,830 --> 00:31:49,590
I want you to kill my sister.

203
00:31:51,230 --> 00:31:52,949
Why?

204
00:31:52,950 --> 00:31:56,150
There are 12 seats
at the high table.

205
00:31:57,270 --> 00:32:00,150
Camorra, mafia, and Ndrangheta.

206
00:32:01,750 --> 00:32:03,950
The Chinese, the Russian.

207
00:32:04,870 --> 00:32:07,070
When my father died...

208
00:32:08,430 --> 00:32:10,710
He willed his seat to her.

209
00:32:12,110 --> 00:32:14,989
She represents camorra now.

210
00:32:14,990 --> 00:32:17,430
And I can't help but wonder

211
00:32:18,470 --> 00:32:21,230
what I might accomplish
in her stead.

212
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:28,190
You want me to kill
Gianna d'Antonio?

213
00:32:30,590 --> 00:32:32,070
I could never do it.

214
00:32:32,630 --> 00:32:34,389
She is my blood.

215
00:32:34,390 --> 00:32:36,349
I still love her.

216
00:32:36,350 --> 00:32:38,029
It can't be done.

217
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:42,269
She's in Rome for
her coronation.

218
00:32:42,270 --> 00:32:43,949
You will take the
catacombs in...

219
00:32:43,950 --> 00:32:46,709
It doesn't matter where she is.

220
00:32:46,710 --> 00:32:52,629
That's why I need the ghost,
<i>Lo Spettro, John wick.</i>

221
00:32:52,630 --> 00:32:54,710
That's why I need you.

222
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:57,549
Do this for me,

223
00:32:57,550 --> 00:32:59,670
and your marker is honored.

224
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:02,550
What say you?

225
00:33:09,830 --> 00:33:11,870
Never one to waste words.

226
00:33:27,350 --> 00:33:30,110
Fifty-nine, zero, 3.5.

227
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:29,680
Happy hunting!

228
00:35:15,010 --> 00:35:18,110
Welcome to the
Continental of Rome.

229
00:35:18,130 --> 00:35:20,629
How might I be of assistance?

230
00:35:20,630 --> 00:35:23,330
I would like a room.

231
00:35:28,030 --> 00:35:29,510
Jonathan!

232
00:35:30,510 --> 00:35:32,190
Julius.

233
00:35:33,950 --> 00:35:35,990
Ciao. Nice to see you.

234
00:35:41,350 --> 00:35:44,630
I fail to recall the last
time you were in Rome.

235
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:47,270
And here I'd heard

236
00:35:47,630 --> 00:35:49,270
you had retired.

237
00:35:50,390 --> 00:35:52,869
I had.

238
00:35:52,870 --> 00:35:56,390
Then humor me with
but one question.

239
00:36:05,750 --> 00:36:07,110
No.

240
00:36:09,310 --> 00:36:10,710
All right, then.

241
00:36:15,630 --> 00:36:18,990
One of our finest rooms.

242
00:36:25,470 --> 00:36:27,070
And enjoy your stay.

243
00:36:34,310 --> 00:36:35,510
Mr. wick.

244
00:36:54,270 --> 00:36:55,429
Is the Sommelier in?

245
00:36:55,430 --> 00:36:57,350
I have never known
him not to be.

246
00:37:12,550 --> 00:37:14,270
Good afternoon, Mr. wick.

247
00:37:15,590 --> 00:37:17,069
It's been a long time.

248
00:37:17,070 --> 00:37:18,509
I'd like a tasting.

249
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:21,590
I am quite excited to
show you something.

250
00:37:22,750 --> 00:37:23,990
First...

251
00:37:29,870 --> 00:37:31,829
<i>Good morning, Mr. Wick!</i>

252
00:37:31,830 --> 00:37:32,869
Hi, Angelo.

253
00:37:32,870 --> 00:37:34,430
Welcome back to Rome.

254
00:37:35,530 --> 00:37:37,029
Would you be in
need of a new suit?

255
00:37:37,030 --> 00:37:38,709
I am.

256
00:37:38,710 --> 00:37:41,029
I know of your past fondness
for the German varietals,

257
00:37:41,030 --> 00:37:45,430
but I can wholeheartedly endorse
the new breed of Austrians.

258
00:37:45,870 --> 00:37:49,629
Glock .34 and .26.

259
00:37:49,630 --> 00:37:52,589
This is the original map
of the d'Antonio estate.

260
00:37:52,590 --> 00:37:55,110
Here, you have all
the ancient ruins.

261
00:37:57,910 --> 00:38:01,069
Tell me, Mr. wick, is this a
formal event or a social affair?

262
00:38:01,070 --> 00:38:02,189
Social.

263
00:38:02,190 --> 00:38:04,909
And is this for day or evening?

264
00:38:04,910 --> 00:38:07,229
I need one for day
and one for night.

265
00:38:07,230 --> 00:38:09,309
Recontoured grips.

266
00:38:09,310 --> 00:38:12,429
Flared magwell for
easier reloads.

267
00:38:12,430 --> 00:38:14,790
And I know you'll appreciate
the custom porting.

268
00:38:17,390 --> 00:38:18,989
What's next?

269
00:38:18,990 --> 00:38:22,629
I need something
robust. Precise.

270
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:26,429
"Robust. Precise."

271
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:31,669
This is the map of the temple
and catacombs underneath.

272
00:38:31,670 --> 00:38:33,389
- In what style?
- Italian.

273
00:38:33,390 --> 00:38:35,149
- How many buttons?
- Two.

274
00:38:35,150 --> 00:38:36,929
- Trousers?
- Tapered.

275
00:38:36,930 --> 00:38:38,530
How about the lining?

276
00:38:38,670 --> 00:38:40,070
Tactical.

277
00:38:40,870 --> 00:38:44,429
Ar-15, 11.5-inch.

278
00:38:44,430 --> 00:38:47,309
Compensated with an
ion-bonded bolt carrier.

279
00:38:47,310 --> 00:38:50,429
Trijicon accupoint with
one-six magnification.

280
00:38:50,430 --> 00:38:54,549
And this is the
modern blueprint.

281
00:38:54,550 --> 00:38:57,830
There are one, two, three gates.

282
00:39:00,070 --> 00:39:03,029
Silicon carbide discs.
Ceramic matrices.

283
00:39:03,030 --> 00:39:04,549
Accompanying laminates.

284
00:39:04,550 --> 00:39:06,509
Cutting-edge body armor.

285
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:10,029
We just sew it between the
fabric and the lining.

286
00:39:10,030 --> 00:39:12,830
Zero penetration. However...

287
00:39:13,870 --> 00:39:15,549
Quite painful, I'm afraid.

288
00:39:15,550 --> 00:39:18,789
Could you recommend anything
for the end of the night?

289
00:39:18,790 --> 00:39:21,269
Something big, bold.

290
00:39:21,270 --> 00:39:24,350
May I suggest the Benelli M4?

291
00:39:28,350 --> 00:39:31,149
Custom bolt carrier release
and charging handle.

292
00:39:31,150 --> 00:39:34,790
Textured grips, should
your hands get wet.

293
00:39:37,230 --> 00:39:38,870
An Italian classic.

294
00:39:39,550 --> 00:39:40,549
Dessert?

295
00:39:40,550 --> 00:39:43,389
Dessert.

296
00:39:43,390 --> 00:39:47,310
The finest cutlery.
All freshly stoned.

297
00:39:56,150 --> 00:39:57,710
Well done.

298
00:39:57,711 --> 00:39:59,630
Could you do a rush
order? I sure can.

299
00:39:59,631 --> 00:40:01,510
Where would you like
to have it sent?

300
00:40:01,511 --> 00:40:02,670
The hotel.

301
00:40:02,671 --> 00:40:04,910
Shall I have everything
sent to your room?

302
00:40:04,911 --> 00:40:07,511
Yes. Thank you. Excellent.

303
00:40:08,711 --> 00:40:10,071
Mr. wick?

304
00:40:13,391 --> 00:40:15,471
Do enjoy your party.

305
00:44:00,111 --> 00:44:01,351
Good evening.

306
00:44:02,151 --> 00:44:04,151
Are you enjoying the party?

307
00:44:04,501 --> 00:44:06,201
Excuse me, miss.

308
00:44:06,591 --> 00:44:08,791
Mr. Akoni is waiting.

309
00:44:50,191 --> 00:44:51,951
Mr. Akoni.

310
00:44:56,791 --> 00:44:58,991
Are you enjoying
the festivities?

311
00:45:00,201 --> 00:45:02,401
Thank you for seeing me.

312
00:45:02,911 --> 00:45:04,791
Please. Sit.

313
00:45:08,831 --> 00:45:10,630
Ms. d'Antonio,

314
00:45:10,631 --> 00:45:12,630
you can't just take what
is rightfully mine.

315
00:45:12,631 --> 00:45:14,950
Nothing was taken.

316
00:45:14,951 --> 00:45:18,030
Those among your own came to
us with these territories.

317
00:45:18,031 --> 00:45:20,151
A knife was pressed
to their throats.

318
00:45:20,751 --> 00:45:22,431
Semantics.

319
00:45:22,831 --> 00:45:24,590
Besides...

320
00:45:24,591 --> 00:45:28,191
That blade you speak of was
meant for their children.

321
00:45:29,151 --> 00:45:32,430
They were only meant to watch.

322
00:45:32,431 --> 00:45:36,271
What is yours is now
ours, Mr. akoni.

323
00:45:37,991 --> 00:45:39,351
Now go.

324
00:45:42,031 --> 00:45:43,751
Enjoy the party.

325
00:45:44,871 --> 00:45:46,671
Have some fun.

326
00:45:51,981 --> 00:45:54,970
Why don’t you go to
entertain our guests...

327
00:45:54,971 --> 00:45:57,671
while I freshen up my makeup.

328
00:45:57,971 --> 00:45:59,971
Okay, Signora.

329
00:46:03,381 --> 00:46:06,281
What could I do
without you, Cassian?

330
00:46:42,791 --> 00:46:44,151
John.

331
00:46:45,791 --> 00:46:47,151
Gianna.

332
00:46:52,831 --> 00:46:54,910
There was a time not so long ago

333
00:46:54,911 --> 00:46:58,351
in which I considered
us as friends.

334
00:47:01,511 --> 00:47:03,151
I still do.

335
00:47:06,351 --> 00:47:07,911
Yet here you are.

336
00:47:14,551 --> 00:47:16,791
What brought you back, John?

337
00:47:17,871 --> 00:47:19,551
A marker.

338
00:47:21,271 --> 00:47:22,551
Held by?

339
00:47:24,551 --> 00:47:26,271
Your brother.

340
00:47:33,671 --> 00:47:35,231
Tell me, John.

341
00:47:35,751 --> 00:47:37,351
This marker...

342
00:47:38,631 --> 00:47:40,311
Is it how you got out?

343
00:47:42,791 --> 00:47:44,750
And what was her name,

344
00:47:44,751 --> 00:47:47,631
this woman whose life
has ended my own?

345
00:47:49,711 --> 00:47:51,351
Helen.

346
00:47:52,111 --> 00:47:53,431
"Helen."

347
00:47:56,151 --> 00:47:57,951
This Helen...

348
00:47:59,591 --> 00:48:02,791
Was she worth the price
that you now seek to pay?

349
00:48:09,231 --> 00:48:10,711
Now,

350
00:48:13,031 --> 00:48:16,190
let me tell you what
happens when I die.

351
00:48:16,191 --> 00:48:19,471
Santino will lay claim
to my seat at the table.

352
00:48:20,671 --> 00:48:22,471
He will take New York.

353
00:48:24,111 --> 00:48:28,671
And you will have been the
one who gifted it to him.

354
00:49:16,871 --> 00:49:19,431
What would your Helen
think about that, John?

355
00:49:37,671 --> 00:49:40,551
What would your Helen
think about you?

356
00:49:40,871 --> 00:49:42,191
Hmm?

357
00:49:56,431 --> 00:49:58,071
Why?

358
00:50:05,431 --> 00:50:07,871
Because I lived my life my way.

359
00:50:09,231 --> 00:50:11,511
And I will die my way.

360
00:50:25,672 --> 00:50:28,592
Do you fear damnation, John?

361
00:50:30,312 --> 00:50:31,632
Yes.

362
00:50:38,032 --> 00:50:40,071
You know,

363
00:50:40,072 --> 00:50:43,592
I always thought I
could escape it.

364
00:50:45,232 --> 00:50:47,432
That I'd see it coming.

365
00:50:50,712 --> 00:50:52,592
That I'd see you.

366
00:52:02,192 --> 00:52:03,712
John?

367
00:52:08,672 --> 00:52:10,032
Cassian.

368
00:52:12,472 --> 00:52:13,792
You working?

369
00:52:16,032 --> 00:52:17,352
Yeah.

370
00:52:17,872 --> 00:52:19,112
You?

371
00:52:20,112 --> 00:52:21,472
Yeah.

372
00:52:24,592 --> 00:52:25,952
Good night?

373
00:52:28,392 --> 00:52:29,872
Afraid so.

374
00:52:31,672 --> 00:52:33,512
I'm sorry to hear that.

375
00:55:27,632 --> 00:55:29,352
Loose ends?

376
00:55:32,112 --> 00:55:34,312
Just one.

377
00:55:36,232 --> 00:55:37,872
Yeah...

378
00:59:49,190 --> 00:59:51,190
You're not havin' a good
night, are you, John?

379
01:02:11,109 --> 01:02:12,349
Gentlemen!

380
01:02:13,989 --> 01:02:15,469
Gentlemen!

381
01:02:26,869 --> 01:02:28,908
Do I need to remind you

382
01:02:28,909 --> 01:02:30,348
that there will be no business

383
01:02:30,349 --> 01:02:32,589
conducted on the
continental grounds?

384
01:02:34,269 --> 01:02:35,469
No,<i> signore.</i>

385
01:02:36,349 --> 01:02:37,749
No, sir.

386
01:02:41,069 --> 01:02:45,429
Now, may I suggest a
visit to the bar,

387
01:02:46,349 --> 01:02:48,109
so you can calm yourselves.

388
01:02:52,069 --> 01:02:53,869
Gin, wasn't it?

389
01:02:54,589 --> 01:02:55,949
Yes.

390
01:02:57,269 --> 01:02:59,589
Bourbon, right?

391
01:03:01,309 --> 01:03:02,589
Yeah.

392
01:03:27,909 --> 01:03:29,549
I had a marker.

393
01:03:31,269 --> 01:03:32,589
Whose?

394
01:03:33,389 --> 01:03:35,148
Her brother.

395
01:03:39,828 --> 01:03:41,188
I see.

396
01:03:42,588 --> 01:03:44,508
You had no choice.

397
01:03:48,708 --> 01:03:51,308
He wants her seat at the table.

398
01:03:52,588 --> 01:03:54,508
He'll get it now.

399
01:03:57,108 --> 01:03:58,468
Yeah.

400
01:03:59,868 --> 01:04:01,228
Yeah.

401
01:04:03,428 --> 01:04:05,068
So you're free.

402
01:04:11,428 --> 01:04:12,748
Am I?

403
01:04:15,028 --> 01:04:16,268
No.

404
01:04:17,908 --> 01:04:19,428
Not at all.

405
01:04:21,388 --> 01:04:25,268
You killed my ward.
Someone I was close to.

406
01:04:27,828 --> 01:04:29,628
An eye for an eye, John.

407
01:04:30,788 --> 01:04:32,588
You know how it goes.

408
01:04:34,588 --> 01:04:35,828
Yeah.

409
01:04:41,788 --> 01:04:43,548
I'll make it quick.

410
01:04:44,708 --> 01:04:46,188
I promise.

411
01:04:47,788 --> 01:04:49,708
I appreciate that.

412
01:04:50,628 --> 01:04:52,788
I'll try and do the same.

413
01:05:01,628 --> 01:05:03,148
This round's on me.

414
01:05:05,988 --> 01:05:08,428
Consider it a
professional courtesy.

415
01:05:31,378 --> 01:05:34,578
<i>Having a tough night?</i>

416
01:05:37,388 --> 01:05:40,588
<i>Can I buy a drink?</i>

417
01:05:40,788 --> 01:05:42,828
No. Thanks.

418
01:05:47,808 --> 01:05:55,808
Not him... me. Be seeing you.

419
01:05:58,407 --> 01:06:00,607
Not if I see you first.

420
01:06:43,187 --> 01:06:45,186
<i>Hello, John.</i>

421
01:06:45,187 --> 01:06:47,586
<i>I understand if you are upset.</i>

422
01:06:47,587 --> 01:06:50,106
<i>And I know it might
feel personal.</i>

423
01:06:50,107 --> 01:06:52,506
<i>But what kind of man would I be</i>

424
01:06:52,507 --> 01:06:54,267
<i>if I didn't avenge
my sister's murder?</i>

425
01:06:55,907 --> 01:06:57,427
John?

426
01:07:13,067 --> 01:07:14,546
Could you let management know

427
01:07:14,547 --> 01:07:16,787
I'll be checking out
in the morning.

428
01:07:53,267 --> 01:07:56,226
Operator. How may I
direct your call?

429
01:07:56,227 --> 01:07:58,347
- Accounts payable.
<i>- One moment, please.</i>

430
01:08:10,627 --> 01:08:12,585
Accounts payable.
How may I help you?

431
01:08:12,586 --> 01:08:14,025
<i>I'd like to open an account.</i>

432
01:08:14,026 --> 01:08:16,305
Name on the
account? John wick.

433
01:08:16,306 --> 01:08:18,025
<i>Verification?</i>

434
01:08:18,026 --> 01:08:20,106
<i>9305-05.</i>

435
01:08:21,306 --> 01:08:23,305
<i>State of contract?</i>

436
01:08:23,306 --> 01:08:25,866
Open. <i>Denomination?</i>

437
01:08:27,106 --> 01:08:28,705
Seven million.

438
01:08:28,706 --> 01:08:30,626
Processing. Please hold.

439
01:08:33,826 --> 01:08:36,225
I appreciate the
service. My pleasure.

440
01:08:36,226 --> 01:08:38,506
You will find safe
passage below.

441
01:08:42,146 --> 01:08:44,106
Transportation is
waiting for you.

442
01:08:45,306 --> 01:08:49,706
May you have a safe
journey, Mr. wick.

443
01:09:55,906 --> 01:09:59,106
Sorry, I fucked up.

444
01:10:17,386 --> 01:10:18,666
Order confirmed.

445
01:10:21,986 --> 01:10:24,426
What is this? He
completed the task.

446
01:10:25,226 --> 01:10:27,786
The marker is over.

447
01:10:28,386 --> 01:10:29,745
Mark it.

448
01:10:29,746 --> 01:10:32,904
If Mr. wick isn't
dead already,

449
01:10:32,905 --> 01:10:34,345
he soon will be.

450
01:10:36,625 --> 01:10:39,545
Will you mark it, sir?

451
01:10:52,105 --> 01:10:56,705
You have no idea
what's coming, do you?

452
01:10:57,665 --> 01:11:00,984
I have everyone in New
York looking for him.

453
01:11:00,985 --> 01:11:03,425
I doubt we will see him again.

454
01:11:05,905 --> 01:11:07,425
Do you now?

455
01:11:08,985 --> 01:11:11,864
You stabbed the
devil in the back

456
01:11:11,865 --> 01:11:14,985
and forced him back into the
life that he had just left.

457
01:11:16,705 --> 01:11:19,424
You incinerated the
priest's temple.

458
01:11:19,425 --> 01:11:20,745
Burned it to the ground.

459
01:11:22,225 --> 01:11:25,625
Now he's free of the marker,
what do you think he'll do?

460
01:11:28,025 --> 01:11:30,504
<i>He had a glimpse
of the other side</i>

461
01:11:30,505 --> 01:11:32,104
<i>and he embraced it.</i>

462
01:11:32,105 --> 01:11:34,185
<i>But you,</i> signor<i> d'Antonio...</i>

463
01:11:35,105 --> 01:11:36,425
...took it away from him.

464
01:11:37,105 --> 01:11:38,664
He was already back.

465
01:11:38,665 --> 01:11:41,304
Oh, he came back for
love, not for you.

466
01:11:41,305 --> 01:11:44,584
He owed me. I had every right.

467
01:11:44,585 --> 01:11:47,705
And now he's coming again.

468
01:11:49,545 --> 01:11:51,225
<i>He did tell you not to do this.</i>

469
01:11:54,225 --> 01:11:55,585
He did warn you.

470
01:15:53,023 --> 01:15:57,103
<i>Please notify MTA personnel
of any suspicious activity.</i>

471
01:16:04,543 --> 01:16:06,542
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

472
01:16:06,543 --> 01:16:09,863
<i>The Broad street bound C
train is now arriving.</i>

473
01:16:11,223 --> 01:16:12,662
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

474
01:16:12,663 --> 01:16:16,183
<i>The broad street bound C
train is now arriving.</i>

475
01:16:28,783 --> 01:16:31,103
<i>Next stop, canal street.</i>

476
01:16:50,703 --> 01:16:52,543
<i>This is canal street.</i>

477
01:16:54,463 --> 01:16:57,822
<i>This is the broad
street bound C train.</i>

478
01:16:57,823 --> 01:17:00,423
<i>The next stop is rector street.</i>

479
01:17:24,263 --> 01:17:26,463
<i>This is rector street.</i>

480
01:17:31,142 --> 01:17:34,022
<i>This is the broad
street bound C train.</i>

481
01:17:34,782 --> 01:17:37,182
<i>The next stop is broad street.</i>

482
01:18:56,622 --> 01:18:58,821
<i>This is broad street.</i>

483
01:18:58,822 --> 01:19:01,661
<i>This is the last stop on
the southbound C train.</i>

484
01:19:01,662 --> 01:19:03,941
The blade is in your aorta.

485
01:19:03,942 --> 01:19:06,941
You pull it out, you'll
bleed, and you will die.

486
01:19:06,942 --> 01:19:08,542
<i>This is the end of the line.</i>

487
01:19:11,702 --> 01:19:14,182
Consider this a
professional courtesy.

488
01:19:14,982 --> 01:19:16,861
<i>This is broad street.</i>

489
01:19:16,862 --> 01:19:20,062
<i>This is the last stop on
the southbound C train.</i>

490
01:19:21,702 --> 01:19:23,782
<i>This is the end of the line.</i>

491
01:19:57,661 --> 01:20:01,060
We say things, we see things.

492
01:20:01,061 --> 01:20:04,660
The things you see
are nightmares, man.

493
01:20:04,661 --> 01:20:06,661
Like this one time...

494
01:20:09,541 --> 01:20:11,341
Take me to him.

495
01:20:14,141 --> 01:20:16,261
Tell him it's John wick.

496
01:20:31,461 --> 01:20:34,380
You know, they just...
They put it in everything!

497
01:20:34,381 --> 01:20:36,421
Hey, man. You got a quarter?

498
01:22:22,740 --> 01:22:24,780
As I live and breathe!

499
01:22:25,620 --> 01:22:27,340
John wick.

500
01:22:27,940 --> 01:22:29,180
The man.

501
01:22:29,820 --> 01:22:31,419
The myth.

502
01:22:31,420 --> 01:22:34,339
The legend.

503
01:22:34,340 --> 01:22:36,540
You're not very
good at retiring.

504
01:22:37,100 --> 01:22:39,899
I'm workin' on it.

505
01:22:39,900 --> 01:22:43,179
Mr. wick doesn't remember,
but we met many years ago,

506
01:22:43,180 --> 01:22:45,220
before my ascension...

507
01:22:46,180 --> 01:22:48,940
When I was just a
pawn in the game.

508
01:22:50,580 --> 01:22:53,019
We met and you gave me a gift,

509
01:22:53,020 --> 01:22:55,020
the gift that would
make me a king.

510
01:22:57,340 --> 01:23:00,580
You don't remember, but there I
was, standing in an alleyway.

511
01:23:01,980 --> 01:23:03,700
I didn't even hear you comin'.

512
01:23:06,900 --> 01:23:09,340
You gave me this.

513
01:23:13,060 --> 01:23:15,699
Gift from the boogeyman.

514
01:23:15,700 --> 01:23:18,460
Perfect for every occasion.

515
01:23:20,620 --> 01:23:23,739
But you also gave me a choice.

516
01:23:23,740 --> 01:23:27,539
Pull my gun, shoot you
in the back, and die.

517
01:23:27,540 --> 01:23:30,060
Or keep the pressure
on my neck...

518
01:23:31,260 --> 01:23:32,460
...and live.

519
01:23:34,580 --> 01:23:37,459
And so you see, I survived.

520
01:23:37,460 --> 01:23:42,259
No one sneaks up on me
anymore, thanks to you.

521
01:23:42,260 --> 01:23:45,780
I am all-seeing
and all-knowing.

522
01:23:47,420 --> 01:23:49,700
Then you know why I'm here.

523
01:23:50,620 --> 01:23:54,779
Santino d'Antonio, yes.

524
01:23:54,780 --> 01:23:57,220
Your contract went wide, John.

525
01:23:57,940 --> 01:24:00,779
That's bad for your health.

526
01:24:00,780 --> 01:24:02,660
What's the number
up to now, Earl?

527
01:24:03,740 --> 01:24:07,899
7 million dollars! Damn!

528
01:24:07,900 --> 01:24:11,540
It's Christmas. We're going
to Applebee's after this.

529
01:24:14,460 --> 01:24:16,579
I need your help.

530
01:24:16,580 --> 01:24:20,299
You have eyes begging for change
on every corner in the city.

531
01:24:20,300 --> 01:24:23,658
I'm thinkin' you
can find Santino.

532
01:24:23,659 --> 01:24:26,578
I need you to move
me. Underground.

533
01:24:26,579 --> 01:24:28,658
Get me to him.

534
01:24:28,659 --> 01:24:31,898
How sweet it is!

535
01:24:31,899 --> 01:24:34,618
The boogeyman begging
me for help.

536
01:24:34,619 --> 01:24:36,378
Well, of course, John.

537
01:24:36,379 --> 01:24:39,018
Yes, John. Whatever
you'd like, John.

538
01:24:39,019 --> 01:24:41,979
Would you like a back
rub with that, John?

539
01:24:42,779 --> 01:24:44,419
You're going to help me.

540
01:24:45,339 --> 01:24:47,859
Why the fuck would I do that?

541
01:24:49,139 --> 01:24:51,819
Because I'm the only
one that can help you.

542
01:25:09,339 --> 01:25:11,858
You're gonna help me out?

543
01:25:11,859 --> 01:25:15,658
That's downright upright
of you, Mr. wick.

544
01:25:15,659 --> 01:25:18,139
You sound positively
magnanimous.

545
01:25:19,739 --> 01:25:21,458
But look around you.

546
01:25:21,459 --> 01:25:25,179
How much help does
it look like I need?

547
01:25:33,619 --> 01:25:37,498
It seems to me that the
real question, Mr. wick,

548
01:25:37,499 --> 01:25:41,619
is who in this cruel world of
ours is going to help you?

549
01:25:55,739 --> 01:25:57,218
There's a storm coming.

550
01:25:57,219 --> 01:26:00,538
Not just for me.
For all of us.

551
01:26:00,539 --> 01:26:02,858
For everyone under the table.

552
01:26:02,859 --> 01:26:04,898
Yes, killing someone who has
a seat at the high table

553
01:26:04,899 --> 01:26:06,578
does create a problem.

554
01:26:06,579 --> 01:26:08,538
But it's your problem, baby.

555
01:26:08,539 --> 01:26:13,658
After all, none of my people
sent Gianna d'Antonio

556
01:26:13,659 --> 01:26:15,619
to the hereafter.

557
01:26:16,859 --> 01:26:20,899
That being said, Santino
has her seat now.

558
01:26:21,339 --> 01:26:23,738
And he wants the city.

559
01:26:23,739 --> 01:26:27,618
When he's done uptown, you think
he's gonna stop at 14th street?

560
01:26:27,619 --> 01:26:30,578
We'll just have to take
care of ourselves.

561
01:26:30,579 --> 01:26:33,579
Oh, yeah? For how long?

562
01:26:34,219 --> 01:26:35,699
And how much blood?

563
01:26:36,339 --> 01:26:38,138
You kill Santino,

564
01:26:38,139 --> 01:26:40,739
the camorra, and the
high table come for you.

565
01:26:41,818 --> 01:26:45,098
I kill Santino,
they come for me.

566
01:26:46,178 --> 01:26:49,777
He's offered 7 million dollars
for your life.

567
01:26:49,778 --> 01:26:54,138
7 million dollars is a lot
of money, Mr. wick.

568
01:26:59,738 --> 01:27:02,258
So I guess you have a choice.

569
01:27:02,618 --> 01:27:04,417
You want a war?

570
01:27:04,418 --> 01:27:07,058
Or do you wanna
just give me a gun?

571
01:27:15,818 --> 01:27:21,858
Somebody, please!
Get this man a gun!

572
01:27:28,058 --> 01:27:31,138
Kimber 1911, .45 ACP.

573
01:27:33,098 --> 01:27:35,858
Seven-round capacity.

574
01:27:43,738 --> 01:27:45,777
Seven rounds?

575
01:27:45,778 --> 01:27:49,618
7 million dollars gets
you seven rounds.

576
01:27:50,618 --> 01:27:53,138
That's a million dollars
a round, baby.

577
01:28:04,018 --> 01:28:05,258
Let's go.

578
01:28:06,578 --> 01:28:09,257
Your descent into hell
begins here, Mr. wick.

579
01:28:09,258 --> 01:28:11,057
He's at the museum.

580
01:28:11,058 --> 01:28:12,217
Earl will guide you.

581
01:28:12,218 --> 01:28:14,538
Do be careful on your way down.

582
01:28:15,578 --> 01:28:19,378
Oh, and remember, you owe me.

583
01:28:20,778 --> 01:28:22,818
You don't want me owing you.

584
01:28:51,378 --> 01:28:52,697
Welcome, everyone.

585
01:28:52,698 --> 01:28:55,697
Let us toast to the
future of the high table

586
01:28:55,698 --> 01:28:58,858
and of course, to the
memory of my dear sister.

587
01:29:15,377 --> 01:29:17,097
Nice to see you.

588
01:29:26,417 --> 01:29:28,337
Mr. akoni, how are you?

589
01:30:22,297 --> 01:30:24,056
Wick is here.

590
01:30:24,057 --> 01:30:25,297
Yeah.

591
01:31:14,657 --> 01:31:17,177
You and you, with me. You, go.

592
01:32:29,336 --> 01:32:34,416
<i>Welcome to "reflections of the
soul" at the new modern NYC.</i>

593
01:32:35,496 --> 01:32:37,255
<i>Within this exhibition,</i>

594
01:32:37,256 --> 01:32:40,375
<i>the interplay of light and
the nature of self-images</i>

595
01:32:40,376 --> 01:32:43,055
<i>coalesce to provide
an experience</i>

596
01:32:43,056 --> 01:32:44,735
<i>which will highlight
the fragility</i>

597
01:32:44,736 --> 01:32:48,535
<i>of our perception of space
and our place within it.</i>

598
01:32:48,536 --> 01:32:51,615
<i>We hope through this exhibit
we can provide new insights</i>

599
01:32:51,616 --> 01:32:53,615
<i>into your understanding
of the world,</i>

600
01:32:53,616 --> 01:32:57,175
<i>and just possibly lead
you to deeper reflection</i>

601
01:32:57,176 --> 01:32:58,816
<i>into the nature of self.</i>

602
01:33:08,096 --> 01:33:09,696
My God, John.

603
01:33:09,697 --> 01:33:11,897
You don’t get it.

604
01:33:12,976 --> 01:33:15,815
The marker is complete, John.

605
01:33:15,816 --> 01:33:17,696
You should have just run away.

606
01:33:27,496 --> 01:33:30,016
You know what the
camorra will do to you.

607
01:33:31,256 --> 01:33:33,376
You think you're old testament?

608
01:33:34,016 --> 01:33:35,776
No, John.

609
01:33:37,816 --> 01:33:39,095
No.

610
01:33:41,015 --> 01:33:42,975
Killing me won't
stop the contract.

611
01:33:44,535 --> 01:33:48,495
Killing me will make
it so much worse.

612
01:33:51,095 --> 01:33:52,455
John,

613
01:33:53,495 --> 01:33:55,015
you know what I think?

614
01:33:57,175 --> 01:33:59,614
I think you are addicted to it.

615
01:33:59,615 --> 01:34:00,855
To the vengeance.

616
01:34:17,895 --> 01:34:23,455
<i>Welcome to "reflections of the
soul" at the new modern NYC.</i>

617
01:34:25,895 --> 01:34:27,255
No wife.

618
01:34:28,695 --> 01:34:30,175
No life.

619
01:34:32,255 --> 01:34:33,495
No home.

620
01:34:34,415 --> 01:34:38,135
Vengeance, it's all you have.

621
01:34:39,255 --> 01:34:41,655
You wanted me back.

622
01:34:42,415 --> 01:34:43,655
I'm back.

623
01:37:32,374 --> 01:37:35,493
<i>You are now exiting "reflections of
the soul" at the new modern NYC.</i>

624
01:37:35,494 --> 01:37:38,093
Go. I'll finish this.

625
01:37:38,094 --> 01:37:40,373
<i>We hope that your journey
through the exhibit</i>

626
01:37:40,374 --> 01:37:43,413
<i>has been one of
reflective contemplation</i>

627
01:37:43,414 --> 01:37:45,734
<i>allowing for a new
perspective and insight.</i>

628
01:37:50,134 --> 01:37:53,494
<i>You are now exiting
"reflections of the soul..."</i>

629
01:39:01,181 --> 01:39:05,681
- Be seeing you.
- Sure.

630
01:39:09,653 --> 01:39:13,053
<i>You are now exiting
"reflections of the soul..."</i>

631
01:39:25,293 --> 01:39:27,093
Good evening.

632
01:39:28,373 --> 01:39:30,132
Is the manager in?

633
01:39:30,133 --> 01:39:33,133
The manager is always in.

634
01:39:38,613 --> 01:39:39,893
Winston.

635
01:39:40,773 --> 01:39:42,932
Mr. d'Antonio.

636
01:39:42,933 --> 01:39:45,692
Your evening has been
colorful, I see.

637
01:39:45,693 --> 01:39:49,092
Seeking safe harbor, I presume?

638
01:39:49,093 --> 01:39:51,372
I want his membership
revoked. Now.

639
01:39:51,373 --> 01:39:53,012
In the eyes of this institution,

640
01:39:53,013 --> 01:39:55,732
Mr. wick has breached
no legalities.

641
01:39:55,733 --> 01:39:57,812
Then you know that I have the
right to demand of you...

642
01:39:57,813 --> 01:40:01,852
Nothing. You demand nothing
of me, Mr. d'Antonio.

643
01:40:01,853 --> 01:40:04,813
This kingdom is mine
and mine alone.

644
01:40:07,413 --> 01:40:09,172
All right.

645
01:40:09,173 --> 01:40:12,372
Then enjoy your kingdom,
Winston, while you still can.

646
01:40:12,373 --> 01:40:15,533
And you its privileges, sir.

647
01:40:27,933 --> 01:40:30,573
I'm here to see
Santino d'Antonio.

648
01:40:34,253 --> 01:40:36,613
He's waiting for you
in the lounge, sir.

649
01:41:25,653 --> 01:41:27,452
Duck fat.

650
01:41:27,453 --> 01:41:29,252
Makes all the difference.

651
01:41:29,253 --> 01:41:30,852
Jonathan...

652
01:41:30,853 --> 01:41:32,173
Have you seen the menu here?

653
01:41:33,333 --> 01:41:36,052
Lot of options. Jonathan,
listen to me...

654
01:41:36,053 --> 01:41:39,452
A man can stay here a long time

655
01:41:39,453 --> 01:41:41,692
and never eat the
same meal twice.

656
01:41:41,693 --> 01:41:44,853
Jonathan, just walk away.

657
01:41:47,093 --> 01:41:48,333
Yeah, Jonathan.

658
01:41:49,293 --> 01:41:50,493
Walk...

659
01:41:57,213 --> 01:41:59,333
What have you done?

660
01:42:02,933 --> 01:42:04,173
Finished it.

661
01:42:21,732 --> 01:42:23,571
How was he?

662
01:42:23,572 --> 01:42:26,612
He was a good dog. I have
enjoyed his company.

663
01:42:31,332 --> 01:42:32,692
Let's go home.

664
01:44:05,490 --> 01:44:06,970
Mr. wick?

665
01:44:13,009 --> 01:44:15,289
If you would be so inclined.

666
01:44:48,089 --> 01:44:49,369
Come on, boy.

667
01:44:57,328 --> 01:44:59,808
It has been a
pleasure, Mr. wick.

668
01:45:06,288 --> 01:45:07,928
Goodbye.

669
01:45:43,247 --> 01:45:44,646
Jonathan.

670
01:45:44,647 --> 01:45:46,007
Winston.

671
01:45:47,407 --> 01:45:48,847
What am I lookin' at?

672
01:45:50,927 --> 01:45:53,246
The Camorra's doubled
Santino's open contract.

673
01:45:53,247 --> 01:45:54,647
It's gone international.

674
01:45:55,727 --> 01:45:56,966
High table?

675
01:45:56,967 --> 01:45:58,167
Mmm-hmm.

676
01:45:59,567 --> 01:46:00,807
And the continental?

677
01:46:02,447 --> 01:46:04,566
You killed a man on company
grounds, Jonathan.

678
01:46:04,567 --> 01:46:08,007
You leave me no choice but to
declare you excommunicado.

679
01:46:09,807 --> 01:46:13,606
The doors to any service or provider
in connection with the continental

680
01:46:13,607 --> 01:46:15,767
are now closed to you.

681
01:46:19,286 --> 01:46:21,086
I am so sorry.

682
01:46:23,166 --> 01:46:25,366
Your life is now forfeit.

683
01:46:27,686 --> 01:46:29,806
Then why am I not dead?

684
01:46:30,766 --> 01:46:33,406
Because I deemed it not to be.

685
01:46:36,166 --> 01:46:37,366
Now.

686
01:47:03,525 --> 01:47:06,965
You have one hour. I can't
delay it any longer.

687
01:47:08,325 --> 01:47:10,045
You might need this...

688
01:47:11,925 --> 01:47:13,165
Down the road.

689
01:47:17,325 --> 01:47:18,525
Winston...

690
01:47:19,565 --> 01:47:21,045
Tell them.

691
01:47:21,845 --> 01:47:24,044
Tell them all.

692
01:47:24,045 --> 01:47:26,004
Whoever comes,

693
01:47:26,005 --> 01:47:27,485
whoever it is,

694
01:47:28,285 --> 01:47:30,085
I'll kill them.

695
01:47:30,485 --> 01:47:32,045
I'll kill them all.

696
01:47:35,885 --> 01:47:37,365
'Course you will.

697
01:47:41,525 --> 01:47:42,965
Jonathan.

698
01:47:44,645 --> 01:47:46,325
Winston.

699
01:48:07,765 --> 01:48:09,445
Accounts payable.

700
01:48:11,645 --> 01:48:15,765
One-one-one-one-one.

701
01:48:17,405 --> 01:48:19,565
In one hour.

702
01:48:20,125 --> 01:48:21,485
John wick.

703
01:48:22,885 --> 01:48:25,005
Excommunicado.

704
01:48:47,565 --> 01:48:50,965
Order 11111 confirmed.
